         <abstract>
            <p>Let $f$ be a monotone and strictly convex (or concave) function on a real interval and let $g$ be the inverse function. Let $I(x) = x$. For $\phi$ a real valued function and $N$ a positive integer let $\phi_N(x)$ denote the rounding of $\phi(x)$ to $N$ significant figures. Let $h = g_N \circ f_N$, the composition of $f_N$ and $g_N$. It is shown that $$h \circ h \circ I_N = h \circ h \circ h \circ I_N,$$ and that equality can fail for fewer iterations.</p>
          </abstract>
